  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0ddd \u0dc4\u0dcf PUCSL \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0db4\u0dca \u0d9a\u0db8\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Before Litro and PUCSL Coop Committee",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Many parliamentary committees, including the Committee on Public Affairs of the Parliament or COPE Committee, the Committee on Government Accounts or COPE Committee, are scheduled to meet this week.",
        "Accordingly, Litro Gas Lanka Limited and Litro Gas Terminal Lanka Limited have been called before the Coop Committee which is scheduled to meet tomorrow (05). The COPE Committee meets under the chairmanship of its Chairman Member of Parliament (Professor) Mr. Charita Herath.",
        "Also, the Ministry of Transport and Highways has been called to the Government Accounts Committee which will meet on the same day under the chairmanship of Member of Parliament (Professor) Honorable Tissa Witharana.",
        "The Advisory Committee of the Ministry of Urban Development and Housing is also scheduled to meet tomorrow under the chairmanship of Minister Prasanna Ranatunga.",
        "In addition to that, the Finance Committee of the Government will also meet on that day under the chairmanship of its Chairman, Member of Parliament Mr. Anura Priyadarshana Yapa, and the Department of Inland Revenue has been summoned before that committee.",
        "Meanwhile, the Public Utility Commission has been called before the COPE Committee which is scheduled to meet on the 6th."
      ],
